src/engine/client\library\clientGame\src\shared\object\CellObject.cpp-169-	{
src/engine/client\library\clientGame\src\shared\object\CellObject.cpp-170-		const CellProperty* const cellProperty = getCellProperty ();

codex
The shared light routing confirms interior cell lights can explicitly opt out of precalculated shaders: `CellObject` creates diffuse lights with `setAffectsShadersWithPrecalculatedVertexLighting(false)`, while specular-only companions opt out of non-precalc. That explains how a precalc building draw can legitimately receive an empty bitset if no precalc-affecting lights are enabled.
