codex
At this point the call graph is clear: `listSz=0` is not itself a D3D11-only drop, because the shared sorter makes that decision before either renderer sees the draw. The renderer divergence is after that: D3D9 treats precalc shaders as a full-ambient mode during static-shader apply; D3D11 currently has no equivalent shader-driven full-ambient switch.
